rules.sql: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM (SELECT id, category, ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY category ORDER BY numeric_col), RANK() OVER (PARTITION BY category ORDER BY numeric_col), DENSE_RANK() OVER (PARTITION BY category ORDER BY numeric_col), PERCENT_RANK() OVER (PARTITION BY category ORDER BY numeric_col), CUME_DIST() OVER (PARTITION BY category ORDER BY numeric_col), NTILE(500) OVER (PARTITION BY category ORDER BY numeric_col), LAG(numeric_col, 10) OVER (PARTITION BY category ORDER BY id), LEAD(numeric_col, 10) OVER (PARTITION BY category ORDER BY id), FIRST_VALUE(numeric_col) OVER (PARTITION BY category ORDER BY numeric_col ROWS BETWEEN UNBOUNDED PRECEDING AND CURRENT ROW), LAST_VALUE(numeric_col) OVER (PARTITION BY category ORDER BY numeric_col ROWS BETWEEN CURRENT ROW AND UNBOUNDED FOLLOWING), SUM(numeric_col) OVER (PARTITION BY category ORDER BY id ROWS BETWEEN 500 PRECEDING AND 500 FOLLOWING) FROM stress_test_data WHERE id <= 1000000)

SELECT category, SUM(POWER(numeric_col, 6)), SUM(EXP(numeric_col/50000000)), SUM(LOG(GREATEST(numeric_col, 1)) * LOG(GREATEST(numeric_col, 1)) * LOG(GREATEST(numeric_col, 1)) * LOG(GREATEST(numeric_col, 1))), SUM(SQRT(SQRT(SQRT(SQRT(ABS(numeric_col)))))), SUM(SIN(numeric_col/2000000) * COS(numeric_col/2000000) * TAN(numeric_col/2000000) * SIN(numeric_col/3000000)), SUM(TAN(numeric_col/200000000) * TAN(numeric_col/200000000) * TAN(numeric_col/200000000) * TAN(numeric_col/200000000)), AVG(POWER(numeric_col, 5) + SQRT(ABS(numeric_col)) + LOG(GREATEST(numeric_col, 1)) + EXP(numeric_col/100000000)), STDDEV(LOG(GREATEST(numeric_col, 1)) * SQRT(ABS(numeric_col)) * SIN(numeric_col/1000000)) FROM stress_test_data WHERE id <= 1600000 GROUP BY category ORDER BY SUM(POWER(numeric_col, 6)) DESC

SELECT category, COUNT(*) FROM stress_test_data WHERE REGEXP_LIKE(text_col, '^Text_Value_[0-9]{1,7}$') AND REGEXP_LIKE(REVERSE(text_col), '^[0-9]{1,7}_eulaV_txeT$') AND LENGTH(REPLACE(REPLACE(REPLACE(REPLACE(REPLACE(REPLACE(REPLACE(REPLACE(REPLACE(REPLACE(REPLACE(REPLACE(text_col, 'T', ''), 'e', ''), 'x', ''), 't', ''), '_', ''), 'V', ''), 'a', ''), 'l', ''), 'u', ''), 'e', ''), '0', ''), '1', '')) > 0 AND CONTAINS(UPPER(LOWER(UPPER(LOWER(UPPER(LOWER(text_col)))))), 'VALUE') AND SUBSTRING(text_col, 1, 15) LIKE 'Text_Value_%' AND id <= 1300000 GROUP BY category HAVING COUNT(*) > 1000
